<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; $25,000 
REWARD OFFERED IN SLAYING OF WOMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles City Council offered a $25,000 reward Wednesday for 
information leading to the arrest of suspects who killed a North Hills woman 
outside a Bible study class last year.  
</P>
<P>
 Laurie Myles was slain Sept. 16 in front of her 9-year-old son, despite 
complying with a demand to hand over her purse.  
</P>
<P>
 Councilman Hal Bernson made the motion to post the reward, and said he hopes 
it will motivate any witnesses to contact investigators. 
</P>
</TEXT>
