<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEXIST WINE LAW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * During a recent tour through the Napa Valley, I learned of an archaic law, a 
leftover from Prohibition days, wherein a male resident of California may, for 
his own use, produce wine in his home.A single male may produce 100 gallons 
year, a married male 200 gallons a year. In contrast, a woman may not produce 
any wine at all. The production for personal use requires a state license.  
</P>
<P>
 I would hope one of our more progressive lawmakers would set about removing 
this sexist law from the state books, which would probably bring about 
gratitude from female constituents. 
</P>
<P>
 LOIS FLYNN 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Niguel 
</P>
</TEXT>
