<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; ENGLAND; PRINCESS DI HELPS SAVE DROWNING MAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Princess Diana is being hailed as a heroine for helping to save a drowning 
vagrant. The princess was on her way home from a jog in London's Regents Park 
on Sunday when tourists flagged her car, pointed to a bridge over the narrow 
lake and said someone had fallen in.Diana, still in running shoes and shorts, 
reportedly told her chauffeur to call police on the car phone, then dashed to 
the bridge where she was joined by Kari Kotila, 29, a Finnish student living in 
London. Kotila, followed by Diana, climbed over the parapet of the bridge onto 
the bank of the lake. The Finn then swam to the 42-year-old Irish vagrant, by 
then unconscious, and towed him to the bank. 
</P>
