<P>
PREP GOLF / CITY CHAMPIONSHIP; ANGEL CRUISES, GRANADA HILLS WINS AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE ELLING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Darren Angel of Granada Hills High decided to hold nothing back on the final 
hole of the City Section golf championships. 
</P>
<P>
 Angel tried to drive the green on the 350-yard par four and came up just 
short.Other than that, precious little went wrong. 
</P>
<P>
 Angel shot his second consecutive three-under 69 Thursday at Knollwood Country 
Club in Granada Hills to win the individual title by 10 shots. 
</P>
<P>
 By the time he teed off at No. 18, the title was won. So why not let her rip? 
</P>
<P>
 "I had to do it," said Angel, grinning. "I've driven (the green) before." 
</P>
<P>
 He has been in the winner's circle before too. Last year, as a sophomore, he 
won the individual crown and led Granada Hills to the team title. The 
Highlanders won the title again with a five-man total of 804, edging Grant by 
two shots. 
</P>
<P>
 Angel's score could have been even better -- he missed a half-dozen putts from 
12 feet or less. Angel, the L.A. City junior champion, set the course record at 
Knollwood two months ago with a 63. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott Golditch of Taft shot 73 to finish second individually at 148. STEVE 
ELLING 
</P>
