 Mazda Announces Recall: The car maker said it is recalling more than 252,000 
sedans that may need repairs on front-door latch mechanisms. The action extends 
to 202,445 of its 1988-91 model 626 sedans and 50,176 of its 1988-89 model 929 
luxury sedans. The company said the doors on the cars may come open 
unexpectedly because the outer door handles may fail. 
