<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION TENNIS PLAYOFFS; MISSION VIEJO WINS LAST SET TO UPSET CORONA 
DEL MAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mission Viejo got a victory in the last set to upset fourth-seeded Corona del 
Mar, 10 2/3-10 1/3, in a Southern Section Division I boys' tennis match 
Thursday at Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Viejo's doubles team of Fernando Machuca and Christian Fernandez 
defeated Corona del Mar's Tyler Stonebreaker and Greg Coleman in the last set, 
6-3. Mission Viejo won six of nine sets in doubles. 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Viejo (11-9) started the season, 1-7. The Diablos, the second-place 
team from the South Coast League, advanced to play Beverly Hills match Tuesday 
in the quarterfinals. Beverly Hills beat San Clemente, 17 2/3-3 1/3, also 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar, the champion of the Sea View League, finished 18-3. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Division I matches: 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills 15, Woodbridge 6 -- Dana Hills used a little incentive and a lot of 
talent to defeat Woodbridge at North Lake Country Club in Irvine. The Dolphins, 
who had beaten Woodbridge (16-6) this season, 17 2/3-3 1/3, were upset about a 
quote from Warrior Coach Joan Willett that appeared this week in a newspaper: 
"Our chances of winning are good. They had a great day against us last time and 
other teams in our league have played them close." 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills players came out to prove they are seeded third for a reason. 
</P>
<P>
 "The things that were in the paper a few days ago gave our team more incentive 
to go out and win," Dolphin Coach John Stephens said. "I knew they would play 
us tougher this time, but we've been working hard to get where we are." 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills (21-0) came out strong, losing only two sets in the first round and 
one in the second to take a 10 1/3-3 2/3 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Doubles player Carlos Betancourt got sick at lunch but played anyway. He and 
Justin Rimel won their first two sets at No. 3 doubles, 6-4, 6-0, but lost to 
Woodbridge's No. 1 Adam Call and A.J. Thoryk, 6-3. Call and Thoryk swept their 
sets, 6-4, 6-3, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills faces University (16-4) Tuesday in the quarterfinals. MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</TEXT>
