<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION BADMINTON PLAYOFFS; CORONA DEL MAR DEFEATS MARINA IN 
QUARTERFINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JANE HUANG 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Corona del Mar's No. 1 boys' double team of Tim Wertin and Jason Eggleston won 
a decisive match over Marina's No. 1 team of Jeremy Sandy and Alan Huang to 
lead the host Sea Kings to a 12-7 victory in the Southern Section Division I 
badminton quarterfinals Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sea Kings will face defending section champion Alhambra Keppel Monday in 
the semifinals.Keppel beat Bolsa Grande, 14-5, also Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our team did great," Corona del Mar Coach Pat Wilson said. "When our No. 1 
doubles team beat Marina's No. 1 team, I think it was a big break for us." 
</P>
<P>
 Wertin and Eggleston won the first game, 15-9. Sandy and Huang, Southern 
Section boys' doubles semifinalists, took the second game, 15-11. Wertin and 
Eggleston regrouped and won the third game, 15-5. 
</P>
<P>
 "We tried to move them around and get more quick shots," Wertin said of the 
third game. "We tried to control the birdie, and that was the key to our win." 
</P>
<P>
 With the victory, the Sea Kings jumped to a 7-1 lead, after victories in boys' 
and girls' singles and Nos. 1 and 3 mixed doubles. Allysun Turner clinched the 
victory for the Sea Kings with an 11-12, 11-3, 11-5 victory over Kelly 
Nedderman in girls' singles. 
</P>
<P>
 Jerome Payyak swept his singles matches for the Sea Kings, and teamed with 
Kerry Smith to win at mixed doubles. Smith and partner Trina Howard also swept 
their doubles matches. 
</P>
<P>
 Wertin and Eggleston won their second doubles match with a 15-2, 18-14 victory 
over Chin Pham and Son Huyuk. JANE HUANG 
</P>
</TEXT>
