<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; ANGELS; LACHEMANN MAKES GRAHE CLOSER AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The hiring of Lachemann immediately has created speculation that left-handed 
starter Jim Abbott could be returning to the Angels. 
</P>
<P>
 Abbott, who's eligible for free agency after the season, practically worships 
Lachemann, and has told friends that returning to Anaheim has become an 
attractive alternative.The Detroit Tigers still are considered the front-runner 
for Abbott's services, but the Angels are expected to make a bid for him. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Kansas City Royals might have the best bargain in baseball at third base 
with Gary Gaetti, who began the game batting .308 with six homers and a 
team-high 30 runs batted in. The Royals are paying Gaetti only $109,000, while 
the Angels are picking up the remainder of his $3-million contract. BOB 
NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</TEXT>
