<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIVE LOCALS WILL BE AT SEAL BEACH VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former UCLA standouts Marissa Hatchett and Elaine Youngs are among five Orange 
County athletes competing in the Bud Light women's four-player beach volleyball 
tour stop at the Seal Beach Pier this weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 The two-day, round-robin tournament begins at 10 a.m. Saturday, with the final 
scheduled for 2 p.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Hatchett, a former Sunny Hills standout, plays for Team Champion. Team Paul 
Mitchell's lineup includes Youngs, a former El Toro player and now a member of 
the U.S. national team, and Irvine's Bev Oden. Oden's sister, Kim, plays for 
Team Sony with former Ocean View standout Tammy Liley. 
</P>
<P>
 The five-team tournament offers a $30,000 purse. Admission is free. MIKE 
REILLEY 
</P>
