<P>
 Oxnard police arrested eight residents Thursday in a raid of homes near the 
corner of Cooper Road and Hayes Avenue, an area that has suffered from chronic 
problems with drugs and violence, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 About 11:20 a.m., police raided five buildings, serving search warrants that 
stemmed from a monthlong undercover narcotics investigation, according to a 
statement from the department. 
</P>
