 They found several grams of heroin, about an ounce of cocaine, two handguns, a 
rifle and $1,500 in cash during the sweep, police said. Officers raided a cafe 
and two homes on Hayes Avenue and nearby businesses on Garfield Avenue and 
Grant Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The undercover investigation was part of a state-funded program aimed at 
ridding La Colonia of drug traffic, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Arrested were Javier Garcia Rodriguez, 40; Goddredo Reyes Mejorado, 47; 
Silvestre Amaya Perez, 26; Georgina Gaytan Verduzco, 23; Manuel Tarazon Gomez, 
56; Samuel Rico Rodriguez, 22; Pedro Marron Zamora, 27, and Javier Mendoza 
Sanchez, 20, all of Oxnard. MATTHEW MOSK 
