<P>
 Upcoming Events 
</P>
<P>
 Today: Thousand Oaks Republican Women, Federated will hold a combination 
fund-raiser and fashion gala. The fashion models will include several wives of 
candidates seeking local, state and federal offices who will serve as their 
escorts. Westlake Inn in Westlake Village; 32001 Agoura Road; 11:30 a.m. $25 
per person. Reservations: 497-0500. 
</P>
<P>
 Saturday: Candidates competing in local and county races will participate in 
an old-fashioned political stump-speech forum at Carlson's Building Materials 
in Thousand Oaks; 1526 Thousand Oaks Blvd.; 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. Information: 
495-5593. 
</P>
<P>
 Sunday: Mary Barreto, an incumbent of the Oxnard Elementary School District 
school board, will launch her reelection campaign with a fund-raiser at 
Hudson's Grill, 2091 N. Oxnard Blvd., Oxnard; 1 to 4 p.m.; $15 per person. 
Reservations: 983-1275 or 984-1252. 
</P>
<P>
 Sunday: The Committee to Elect Chuck Weis, appointed Ventura County 
superintendent of schools, will sponsor a fund-raiser at the Santa Rosa Valley 
home of Twila Cook. 12950 Rancho Vista Court; 1 to 3 p.m.; $10 per person. 
Information: 493-1342. 
</P>
<P>
 Sunday: The Committee to Elect Chuck Weis, appointed Ventura County 
superintendent of schools, will sponsor a barbecue fund-raiser at Long Canyon 
Ranch in Simi Valley; east end of Country Club Drive; 3 to 5 p.m.; $16 per 
person. Information: 520-1706. 
</P>
<P>
 Wednesday: The five candidates competing for the Ventura County supervisor 
seat representing Thousand Oaks, Oak Park and Port Hueneme will participate in 
a public forum sponsored by the Community Foundation for Oak Park. Brookside 
Elementary School; 165 N. Satinwood Street; 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Wednesday: Ventura County supervisor candidate Trudi K. Loh will be the guest 
speaker at the monthly meeting of Concerned Citizens of Thousand Oaks. The 
public is invited. Cameron Center in Thousand Oaks; 288 Greenmeadow Drive; 7 
p.m. Information: 378-7274. 
</P>
