Court judge, will be the host of a fund-raiser at the Camarillo home of John 
and Barbara Morgan; 88 La Patera Drive; 5:30 to 7:30 p.m.; $20 per person. 
Information: 642-5119. 
</P>
<P>
 May 29: Ventura County supervisor candidate H. Jere Robings will hold a 
barbecue fund-raiser at Conejo Creek Park in Thousand Oaks. 1401 E. Janss Road; 
1 to 5 p.m.; $7 per person or $15 per family. Information: 494-8948. 
</P>
<P>
 June 1: Attorney James M. Farley and Assistant Dist. Atty. Colleen Toy White, 
candidates for Ventura County Superior Court judge, will participate in a 
public forum sponsored by the League of Women Voters of Ventura County. Oxnard 
Library Meeting Room; 251 South A Street; 6:30 to 8 p.m. Information: 650-3631. 
</P>
<P>
