<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: 64 GIVES BROOKS GOLF LEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pro Basketball  
</P>
<P>
 In his second NBA season, Golden State guard Latrell Sprewell was named to the 
All-NBA team. He joins Chicago's Scottie Pippen, Houston's Hakeem Olajuwon, and 
the Utah pair of Karl Malone and John Stockton on the team selected by 
sportswriters and broadcasters. 
</P>
<P>
 Selected to the second team were San Antonio's David Robinson, Seattle's Shawn 
Kemp, Sacramento's Mitch Richmond and the Phoenix pair of Charles Barkley and 
Kevin Johnson. Shaquille O'Neal of Orlando headed the third team. 
</P>
<P>
 Net guard Kenny Anderson will have a screw put into his broken left wrist and 
is expected to be ready for training camp next fall. Anderson broke the wrist 
in February of 1993, then re-broke it in December. A third break was discovered 
Tuesday when he complained the wrist hurt during the playoffs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
