<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHORT SPRINT GETS SEARCY TO LONG BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Troy Searcy of Quartz Hill High finished second in a runoff in the boys' 
100-meters dash at Gahr High on Thursday and advanced to Saturday's Southern 
Section Division I track and field championships at Long Beach Veterans 
Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Searcy ran a wind-aided 10.7 seconds to finish behind Jamal Carr (10.3) of 
Muir, but ahead of Anthony Rudolph of West Covina and Tyson Murphy of Santa 
Monica. 
</P>
<P>
 The top two finishers advanced to the Division I final as the eighth and ninth 
qualifiers. 
</P>
<P>
 The runoffs became necessary when section officials discovered Monday that the 
Accutrack timing device malfunctioned early in last Saturday's Division I 
preliminaries, resulting in incorrect times and erroneous seedings for the 
championships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
