<HEADLINE>
<P>
GUNMEN ROB COUPLE AT HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two masked gunmen entered a Northridge home while the residents were watching 
television and robbed them of an undetermined amount of cash and jewelry, 
authorities said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was injured in the robbery, which occurred about 11 p.m. Wednesday in 
the 17000 block of Halstead Street. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the gunmen, who wore nylon over their heads, entered the 
single-story home through a rear door. They pointed their guns and demanded 
valuables from the husband and wife, who were in bed watching television. 
</P>
<P>
 The robbers, who were in the house for about three minutes, escaped on foot 
with a small amount of cash and jewelry from a dresser, said Detective Michael 
Brandt of the Los Angeles Police Department's Devonshire Division. 
</P>
<P>
 "We haven't had a home invasion in quite some time -- at least six months," 
Brandt said. "It's unusual, and we are going to monitor the situation to see 
that it's not repeated." 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the robbers wore dark clothing and described them as having medium 
height and weight. 
</P>
<P>
 There were no suspects late Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
