<HEADLINE>
<P>
MUSTAFA POINTING FOR TITLE; COLLEGE TRACK: MOORPARK DECATHLETE HOPES TO SCORE 
7,000 AND WIN STATE CHAMPIONSHIP. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN ORTEGA, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tallying 7,000 points in the decathlon might seem far-fetched for someone who 
has yet to top 6,500, but Moorpark College Coach Doni Green figures sophomore 
Isaiah Mustafa is ready for the challenge. 
</P>
<P>
 Mustafa will shoot for 7,000 at the state junior college track and field 
championships that start today at Cerritos College.  
</P>
<P>
 The Moorpark sophomore, runner-up in last year's state championships, totaled 
a personal best of 6,417 points to finish second in the Southern California 
championships last month. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Kanowsky of Long Beach City trailed Mustafa by 393 points after six of 
10 events, but finished strongly to win with 6,557 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Mustafa's fall to second began in the discus -- the decathlon's seventh event 
-- when he threw 102 feet 3 inches to Kanowsky's 117-0, and continued in the 
pole vault (11-7 3/4 to 13-3 1/2) and javelin (138-1 to 183-9), but Green says 
Mustafa has improved dramatically in the discus, pole vault and 110-meter high 
hurdles since. 
</P>
<P>
 "He has the potential to score at least 6,800 points if he hits all his 
events," Green said. "And 7,000 is possible with someone like him." 
</P>
<P>
 A score of 6,800 might be needed to win the decathlon. Alphonso Davis of 
Sacramento City totaled 6,698 points to win the Northern California 
championships. 
</P>
<P>
 Mustafa also will compete in the long jump, an event in which he finished 
third in the Southern California championships with a personal best of 23-6 
1/4. 
</P>
<P>
 Sean McKeown (shotput, discus) and Mike Esparza (3,000-meter steeplechase) of 
Moorpark, Isaac Turner (800) of Glendale and Amy Blackburn (discus) of Ventura 
are also expected to contend for top-three finishes. 
</P>
<P>
 Today's meet begins at 2 p.m. with the men's hammer throw, followed by the 
heptathlon 100 hurdles at 2:30. The meet starts at 1 p.m. Saturday with the 
decathlon 110 high hurdles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
