<HEADLINE>
<P>
CSUN'S GILLESPIE, SHANAHAN EARN ALL-CONFERENCE HONORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE ELLING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Northridge baseball standouts Eric Gillespie and Jason Shanahan, who 
tied for the team lead in batting with a .342 average, were selected to the 
All-Western Athletic Conference West Division team. 
</P>
<P>
 Shanahan, a junior first baseman, won the conference triple crown, batting 
.416 in WAC play with six home runs and 30 runs batted in.He led the Matadors 
in homers (nine), RBIs (50) and stolen bases (seven). Shanahan, a switch-hitter 
from Missoula, Mont., homered against each West Division foe. He hit .394 
against left-handers and .318 against right-handers. 
</P>
<P>
 Gillespie, a freshman catcher from Long Beach Millikan High, hit six homers 
and had 42 RBIs, despite spending most of the season batting leadoff. He hit 
safely in 47 of 55 games and led the team with 80 hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Gillespie, who bats left-handed, had 22 multihit games and never went two 
consecutive games without a hit. He struck out only 17 times in 234 at-bats and 
hit safely in 21 of 24 WAC games. 
</P>
<P>
 Gillespie and Shanahan are expected to play this summer for the Mat-su Miners 
of the Alaskan Summer League. 
</P>
<P>
 Wyoming's Jim Gattis, a North Hollywood product, was named the WAC East 
Division coach of the year. STEVE ELLING 
</P>
