<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; VIETNAM; HANOI SENTENCES 11 FOR FRAUD ON MIAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Frenchman and 10 Vietnamese accomplices have been sentenced to prison for 
producing fraudulent remains and documents of U.S. servicemen missing in the 
Vietnam War, a Hanoi newspaper said. Robert Chaillard, a native of France and 
resident of Vietnam, masterminded a scheme in which he misrepresented Asian 
bones and other physical remains as those of American MIAs, according to the 
newspaper. 
