 Rebels stepped up their push for Rwanda's capital in a fierce artillery duel 
that killed 30 people at an overcrowded hospital in a government-held part of 
Kigali and rained shells on the airport and U.N. headquarters.Rebels denied 
having targeted the hospital. A Red Cross medical officer was wounded when his 
