GERMAN MAN DESCRIBES 3 ATTACKERS; SKETCH IS RELEASED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A German man who is unable to speak after a robbery attack that left his wife 
dead told authorities in writing that three teen-agers attacked him, 
authorities said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Klaus Pfleger, 64, of Emmerich, Germany, was able to describe one of the 
attackers well enough for authorities to release a composite sketch.Sketches of 
the other two are likely to be released within days, Riverside County sheriff's 
spokesman Mark Lohman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Lohman described the three assailants as male, 17 to 20 years old, and ranging 
in height from 5 feet, 8 inches to 5 feet, 10 inches. All had dark eyes and 
hair. 
</P>
<P>
 Based on interviews with witnesses who saw the attackers drive along scenic 
California 243, authorities said they were driving a late-model two-door coupe, 
possibly forest green. 
</P>
<P>
 Pfleger and his wife, Gisela, 62, were shot as they gazed out over the San 
Jacinto Mountains near Idyllwild on Monday. Gisela Pfleger was shot in the head 
several times and killed. Her husband was shot once in the shoulder and twice 
in the head. 
