<TEXT>
<P>
 Five people are facing criminal charges in connection with the killing of a 
Long Beach woman who was beaten and stabbed in her Long Beach home last 
December, police said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspects were booked for murder in the Dec. 2 attack on Ruby Chong at her 
residence in the 2100 block of Baltic Avenue, Long Beach Police Detective Logan 
Wren said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police on Wednesday arrested Tabitha Brown, 20, of Ontario. Their 
investigation led them to Brown's sister, Cindy Brown, 18, of Carson, and three 
other Carson teen-agers -- two 17-year-old-boys and a 16-year-old boy whose 
names were withheld because of their ages, said Detective John Boston. He said 
a break in the case came when detectives obtained a warrant for Tabitha Brown's 
arrest on charges of forging several of the victim's checks. 
