<P>
 Former Fed Governor Reportedly Under Investigation: The Federal Reserve System 
is investigating whether former Fed Gov. Wayne Angell received inside 
information about the Fed's activities or simply had a brilliant hunch, 
according to the New York Times.The focus of the inquiry is a report Angell 
wrote a few weeks ago for clients of Bear Stearns, his new employer. In the 
report, he said eight or nine of the 12 regional banks had requested an 
increase in the discount rate. The knowledge that the boards of regional banks 
were pushing to raise the discount rate would be helpful in predicting the vote 
of the Federal Open Market Committee because very few people are close to those 
requests. 
