ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; WORLD CUP BANNERS ON DISPLAY AT PLAZA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hundreds of bright banners are being hung at South Coast Plaza during the next 
week to celebrate the 1994 World Cup soccer games, which will be played in 
various U.S. cities during June and July. 
</P>
<P>
 The largest banner, 1,200 square feet, will be unfurled next week across the 
Bear Street facade of the Crystal Court shopping center.There also will be 
numerous banners inside the center. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 130 lampposts around the South Coast Plaza and Crystal Court 
shopping centers will fly eight-foot banners. 
</P>
<P>
 The banners show soccer players and the American team's mascot: a dog named 
Striker. 
</P>
<P>
 The banners will stay up until after the July 17 soccer finals, said Ellen 
Appel, spokeswoman for South Coast Plaza. 
</P>
<P>
 The World Cup is the most-watched athletic competition worldwide. Finals for 
the World Cup will be at the Rose Bowl.WILLSON CUMMER 
