<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; COLLEGE ALUMNI TO BE HONORED FOR SERVICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Officials for the Rancho Santiago College District will honor two alumni today 
for their service to the community by inducting them into the district's Hall 
of Fame. 
</P>
<P>
 During a private ceremony, district officials will recognize Anaheim 
firefighter Jerry D. Austin and Mary Halvorson, a dean at Rancho Santiago 
College, spokesman Dale Ruhe said. 
</P>
<P>
 Austin graduated from the college's Fire Academy program in 1978 and has 
worked for the Anaheim Fire Department as an arson investigator, fire education 
specialist and acting fire marshal. He was promoted to the rank of battalion 
chief in January. Austin lives in Long Beach and is pursuing a master's degree 
in public administration, Ruhe said. 
</P>
<P>
 Halvorson graduated from Rancho Santiago in 1978 and worked as a nurse for 
several years before returning to the school to teach. She later became the 
assistant dean of applied arts and sciences, a position she has held for two 
years, Ruhe said. 
</P>
<P>
 An accomplished pilot, Halvorson is a member of the Flying Samaritans, a group 
that runs medical clinics in Mexico. She has also worked with single mothers at 
Casa Teresa Home in Orange. She lives in Santa Ana. JON NALICK 
</P>
