MAN DENIES MURDER CHARGES IN DEATH OF GIRLFRIEND'S TODDLER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A house painter pleaded not guilty Thursday to murder in connection with the 
death of his girlfriend's 22-month-old son. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Laudenback, 32, of Newport Beach was arrested after Tyler Jaeger died 
March 25 at Hoag Hospital.A preliminary autopsy showed that the child, who 
Laudenback was baby-sitting, had suffered severe blows to his liver and 
pancreas caused by a blunt instrument. 
</P>
<P>
 A preliminary hearing was set for July 21 in Municipal Court in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Laudenback pleaded not guilty to felony child abuse last month. Authorities 
upgraded the charges to murder a week later and raised his bail to $250,000. He 
remains in custody, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 One week before Tyler's death, Laudenback brought the child to Hoag Hospital 
for treatment of a fractured skull, authorities said. He said at the time that 
Tyler, the son of 22-year-old Karey Jaeger, had fallen accidentally and bumped 
his head.  
</P>
<P>
 Laudenback often baby-sat Tyler while Karey Jaeger went to work in the San 
Gabriel Valley. He was arrested March 25, the day Tyler died, after police said 
they learned of suspicious bruising on Tyler's body and the earlier head 
injury. 
